recordings.rmk: This sound would be difficult to hear in the field, although it is described in "Birds of the World".  I placed a Sennheiser MHK416 about 2 meters from a feeding station and recorded the chip on a Sound Devices 722.  A rather weak song of this same bird is also in this recording.

recordings.loc: Skidaway Island, Chatham County, GA USA
recordings.rmk: This song is truncated, missing two emphatic notes at the end.  It is heard often in early spring in this location. I might speculate that these are last year's  hatch learning the full song, but it is not plastic, nor a subsong.  It is consistent.  As w get further into the breeding cycle the full song dominates.

recordings.loc: Skidaway Island, Chatham County, GA USA
recordings.rmk: Typical song.  This species is a permanent resident in small numbers, and is very often the first one to sing, as early as February in this location.

La Vela De Coro, Colina, Falcón
recordings.rmk:
La grabación es un play back tomado de vídeo, no se modifico.
El habitad son unos arboles de Cuji al lado de una corriente de agua dulce que da al mar a unos 100 metros.
El ave se comporta inquieta entra las ramas mientras busca insectos para alimentarse.
Es un ave migratoria es pequeña con distintivo amarillo en la ganganta,  máscara negra y estrías negras a los lados. Espalda azul gris.
Esta especie se registro por primera ves en Venezuela en 0ctubre 2019, sumando un ave mas para nuestro país.

recordings.rmk: I am assuming this is a Black-and-white Warbler based on the song sounding like a "squeaky wheel" as I learned it years ago.  I have heard so few in the field that I may need double checking.  The recording was not altered.  The bird was mid canopy level in a hardwood forest with some open space between trees.  It was mid day and starting to get warm.  Bird activity overall was low.
